'''Dalip Singh Rana''' (born 27 August 1972), better known by the [[ring name]] '''The Great Khali,''' is an Indian-American<ref>{{cite web |title=The Great Khali becomes a U.S. citizen: photos |url=https://www.wwe.com/inside/overtheropes/the-great-khali-us-citizen-photos#fid-26236125 |website=WWE |accessdate=25 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> [[Professional wrestling|professional wrestler]], [[Wrestling promoter|promoter]], model, and actor who is best known for his work in [[WWE]]. He is also the first Indian to win the [[World Heavyweight Championship (WWE)|World Heavyweight Championship]] in WWE history.

A professional wrestler since 2000, Rana was most notably associated with [[WWE]] from 2006 to 2014 where he performed under the name of "The Great Khali". Before embarking on his professional wrestling career, he was an officer for the [[Punjab Police (India)|Punjab Police]]. He has appeared in four [[Hollywood]] films, two [[Bollywood]] films and several television shows.

== Early life ==
Rana was born to Jwala Ram and his wife Tandi Devi in a [[Punjabis|Punjabi]] [[Hindu]] family of the [[Dhiraina]] village of [[Himachal Pradesh]]'s [[Sirmaur district]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/buzz/mouthful/reporter-jumps-on-table-great-khali-interview-229.html|title=When a reporter jumped on table to take The Great Khali's interview|publisher=|date=3 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=What's common between Sunny Leone and The Great Khali?|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/news/ENT-whats-common-between-sunny-leone-and-the-great-khali-4341186-PHO.html?seq=2&mpage=104|accessdate=14 March 2016|work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] (English edition)|date=7 August 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315004001/http://daily.bhaskar.com/news/ENT-whats-common-between-sunny-leone-and-the-great-khali-4341186-PHO.html?seq=2&mpage=104|archivedate=15 March 2016}}</ref>

Being one of the seven siblings of a poor family, he had to do odd jobs to make ends meet and suffers from [[acromegaly]], which among other effects causes [[gigantism]] and chin protrusion.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/star-wrestler-great-khali-tumor-removed-caused-size/story?id=16874060|title=WWE Star Great Khali's Growth-Inducing Tumor Removed|date=29 July 2012|work=[[ABC News]]|accessdate=14 March 2016}}</ref> When Rana was serving as a security guard in [[Shimla]], he caught the eye of a police officer from the neighbouring State of Punjab that''—''having previously helped several employees of Punjab Police to become international sportspersons''—''got him inducted into the Punjab Police in 1993,<ref name="indiatimes">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/2910680.cms|title=Khali still on Punjab police pay rolls|accessdate=15 June 2008|date=30 March 2008|publisher=The Times of India|first1=Rohit|last1=Mullick}}</ref> and (though Rana was reluctant to leave [[Himachal Pradesh]], his brother was also offered a job in the Punjab Police) once he landed in Punjab's [[Jalandhar]], Rana trained in the local gyms to become a wrestler and soon he got selected for specialised wrestling training in the United States.<ref name="Daily News and Analysis">{{cite news|title=8-FT-HIGH DOORS AWAIT 'THE GREAT KHALI' IN NATIVE VILLAGE|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-8-ft-high-doors-await-the-great-khali-in-native-village-1162883|accessdate=14 March 2016|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=5 May 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314131848/http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-8-ft-high-doors-await-the-great-khali-in-native-village-1162883|archivedate=14 March 2016}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Rana is a Hindu<ref>[http://www.nriinternet.com/NRIwrestling/USA/A_Z/K/Great_Khali/Bio.htm "The Great Khali- His real name is Dalip Singh Rana"]. ''nriinternet.com''.</ref> and has been described as "extremely religious".<ref name="Rajah"/><ref>[http://iskconmauritius.com/node/1399 "Great Khali Appreciates Iskon"], ''Iskcon Mauritius'', 16 March 2011, [https://web.archive.org/web/20121011040903/http://iskconmauritius.com/node/1399 Archive]</ref> He meditates every day and "abhors" alcohol and tobacco.<ref name="BBC1">Guha-Ray, Shantanu. [http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/7384920.stm "Giant wrestler finds fame in India"], ''BBC News'', 6 May 2008, [https://web.archive.org/web/20111022204657/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/7384920.stm Archive]</ref> He was a disciple of Indian spiritual guru [[Ashutosh (spiritual leader)|Ashutosh Maharaj]].<ref name="Guru">[http://www.dnaindia.com/india/special-the-man-who-made-the-great-khali-1163493 "The man who made the Great Khali"]. ''dna''.</ref>

Rana suggested the ring name The Great Khali after the Hindu [[goddess]] [[Kali]], who is associated with eternal energy.<ref name="bbc"/>

Rana's training schedule consists of two hours of [[weight training]], morning and evening, every day, but his diet is unclear, as in some interviews it was claimed he maintains his size on a vegetarian diet<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/7384920.stm|title=BBC NEWS – South Asia – Giant wrestler finds fame in India|work=bbc.co.uk|date=6 May 2008}}</ref> and in other interviews it was claimed he consumes vast quantities of chicken.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100525/jsp/entertainment/story_12482840.jsp|title=Gentle Giant|last=t2|date=25 May 2010|publisher=The Telegraph, Calcutta, India|page=1|accessdate=8 September 2010}}</ref> He has since clarified that he loves vegetarian food, but also consumes meat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wrestlingtruth.com/news/great-khali-debeats-with-indian-media-about-how-fake-wrestling-is/|title=Great Khali Debeats With Indian Media About How Fake Wrestling Is|last=Balderson|first=Keelan|author2=Rajat Sharma|date=22 February 2010|publisher=www.wrestlingtruth.com|page=1|accessdate=8 September 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100224054111/http://wrestlingtruth.com/news/great-khali-debeats-with-indian-media-about-how-fake-wrestling-is/|archivedate=24 February 2010}}</ref>

On 26 July 2012 it was reported that Rana underwent a brain surgery due to a tumor on his [[pituitary gland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://triblive.com/home/2280702-74/singh-tumor-maroon-wrestling-upmc-team-according-condition-khali-led|title=Wrestling star Great Khali has tumor removed at UPMC|publisher=TribLIVE|date=26 July 2012|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref>

Rana became a naturalised U.S. citizen on 20 February 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/videos/the-great-khali-becomes-a-u-s-citizen|title=The Great Khali becomes a U.S. Citizen|publisher=}}</ref>

